mgs360024fSystemTimeManualClockSource.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualClockSource
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualClockSource.description: default: 0, 0 : Use Local Settings, 1 : Use NTP Server.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualLocaltime.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualLocaltime
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualLocaltime.description: Get/Set the system time of the device. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute:Second'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43:05 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43:05 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59, Sec : 0 - 59.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset.description: Get/Set the NTP Time Zone. The value range is between -720 and 780 (minutes).

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time. The value range is between 1 and 1440 (minutes), Default : 60 (minutes).

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsBydatesFrom
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsBydatesTo
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the End time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringDayFrom
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Day From. 0 : Sun, 1 : Mon, 2 : Tue, 3 : Wed, 4 : Thu, 5 : Fri, 6 : Sat.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringWeekFrom
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Week From. 1 : first week, 2, 3, 4, 5 : last week

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringMonthFrom
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Month From. 1 : Jan, 2 : Feb, 3 : Mar, 4 : Apr, 5 : May, 6 : Jun, 7 : Jul, 8 : Aug, 9 : Sep, 10 : Oct, 11 : Nov, 12 : Dec.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringTimeFrom
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Hour:Minute'. ex: 05:43. The value range: Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringDayTo
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Day To. 0 : Sun, 1 : Mon, 2 : Tue, 3 : Wed, 4 : Thu, 5 : Fri, 6 : Sat.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringWeekTo
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Week To. 1 : first week, 2, 3, 4, 5 : last week

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringMonthTo
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Month To. 1 : Jan, 2 : Feb, 3 : Mar, 4 : Apr, 5 : May, 6 : Jun, 7 : Jul, 8 : Aug, 9 : Sep, 10 : Oct, 11 : Nov, 12 : Dec.

mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringTimeTo
mgs360024fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Hour:Minute'. ex: 05:43. The value range: Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

mgs360024fSystemTimeNTPIndex.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeNTPIndex
mgs360024fSystemTimeNTPIndex.description: The index of the ntp entry.

mgs360024fSystemTimeNTPServer.name: mgs360024fSystemTimeNTPServer
mgs360024fSystemTimeNTPServer.description: Get/Set the NTP Time Server1. You can use the IP address or domain name.

mgs360024fSystemAccountUserCreate.name: mgs360024fSystemAccountUserCreate
mgs360024fSystemAccountUserCreate.description: default: 0 0 : None (read only) 1 : Create a user account

mgs360024fSyslogLevel.name: mgs360024fSyslogLevel
mgs360024fSyslogLevel.description: default: 6 (Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fGetCommunity.name: mgs360024fGetCommunity
mgs360024fGetCommunity.description: Get/Set the get-community of the SNMP.

mgs360024fSetCommunityMode.name: mgs360024fSetCommunityMode
mgs360024fSetCommunityMode.description: Get/Set the set-community mode of the SNMP. default : 1, 0: disable, 1: enable.

mgs360024fSetCommunity.name: mgs360024fSetCommunity
mgs360024fSetCommunity.description: Get/Set the set-community of the SNMP.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfTable.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfTable
mgs360024fTrapHostConfTable.description: A list of trap host entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of mgs360024fTrapHostConfNumber.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfEntry.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfEntry
mgs360024fTrapHostConfEntry.description: This is the entry information for trap host.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfIndex.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfIndex
mgs360024fTrapHostConfIndex.description: The index of the trap host entry.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfVersion.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfVersion
mgs360024fTrapHostConfVersion.description: The version of the Trap PDU. Version : 2(SNMPv2c), 3(SNMPv3)

mgs360024fTrapHostConfIPType.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfIPType
mgs360024fTrapHostConfIPType.description: Server IP Type. Default: 4, 4 : IPv4, 6 : IPv6.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfIP.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfIP
mgs360024fTrapHostConfIP.description: This is the IP of the trap host.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfPort.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfPort
mgs360024fTrapHostConfPort.description: This is the receiving-port number of the trap host. range : 1 - 65535.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfCommunity.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfCommunity
mgs360024fTrapHostConfCommunity.description: The community/security name for the trap PDU.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel
mgs360024fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel.description: The Severity Level. 0 : Emerg, 1 : Alert, 2 : Crit, 3 : Error, 4 : Warning, 5 : Notice, 6 : Info, 7 : Debug.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel
mgs360024fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel.description: The Security Level, NoAuthNoPriv, AuthNoPriv, and AuthPriv. 1 : NoAuthNoPriv, 2 : AuthNoPriv, 3 : AuthPriv. Privacy protocol will be configured as 'DES' automatically if security level is 3(AuthPriv).

mgs360024fTrapHostConfAuthPtc.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfAuthPtc
mgs360024fTrapHostConfAuthPtc.description: Authentication Protocol, there are SHA and MD5 supported presently. 1 : MD5, 2 : SHA.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfAuthPassword.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfAuthPassword
mgs360024fTrapHostConfAuthPassword.description: Authentication Password, is used for authenticating. The return value is always '********'. If the authentication protocol is MD5, the length of password should be 8 ~ 32 characters. If the authentication protocol is SHA, the length of password should be 8 ~ 40 characters.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfPrivPtc.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfPrivPtc
mgs360024fTrapHostConfPrivPtc.description: This is the Privacy Protocol, which is used in AuthPriv. Only supports DES. An empty string will be returned if the security level is not 3(AuthPriv). 1 : DES.

mgs360024fTrapHostConfPrivPassword.name: mgs360024fTrapHostConfPrivPassword
mgs360024fTrapHostConfPrivPassword.description: The password is Privacy Key. The return value is always '********'. This Key must be more than 8 characters, and less than 32 characters.

mgs360024fPortConfCurrentSpeed.name: mgs360024fPortConfCurrentSpeed
mgs360024fPortConfCurrentSpeed.description: The current link speed of the port.

mgs360024fPortConfSpeed.name: mgs360024fPortConfSpeed
mgs360024fPortConfSpeed.description: default: 1, 0: disable state, 1: auto, 2: 10 Half, 3: 10 Full, 4: 100 Half, 5: 100 Full, 6: 1G full, only 'Dual Media' port have 7-11 option. Dual Media port default: 7, 7: SFP_Auto_AMS, 8: 100FX_AMS, 9: 1000X_AMS, 10: 100FX, 11: 1000X

mgs360024fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode.name: mgs360024fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode
mgs360024fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode.description: default: 0, Excessive Collision Mode : 0: Discard, 1: Restart, 2: not support.

mgs360024fPortConfPowerControl.name: mgs360024fPortConfPowerControl
mgs360024fPortConfPowerControl.description: default: 0, PowerControl : 0: disable, 1: Actiphy, 2: Dynamic (perfectReach), 3: Enable, 4: not support.

mgs360024fPortConfDescription.name: mgs360024fPortConfDescription
mgs360024fPortConfDescription.description: Interface specific description. Up to 47 characters describing this interface.

mgs360024fGARPStatisticsTable.name: mgs360024fGARPStatisticsTable
mgs360024fGARPStatisticsTable.description: Show the basic GARP port statistics.

mgs360024fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC.name: mgs360024fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC
mgs360024fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC.description: Peer MAC is MAC address of the neighbour Switch from with GARP frame is received.

mgs360024fMirrorMode.name: mgs360024fMirrorMode
mgs360024fMirrorMode.description: default: 0 0: disable 1: enable 2: rx only 3: tx only Setting Tx mirroring for analyzer port has no effect. Tx mirroring ignored

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityACL.name: mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityACL
mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityACL.description: default: 6(Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityACLLog.name: mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityACLLog
mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityACLLog.description: default: 7(Debug) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityAccessMgmt.description: default: 6(Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityAuthFailed.description: default: 4(Warning) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityColdStart.name: mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityColdStart
mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityColdStart.description: default: 4(Warning) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityLACP.description: default: 6(Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityLinkStatus.description: default: 4(Warning) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityLogin.description: default: 6(Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityModuleChange.description: default: 5(Notice) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityNAS.description: default: 6(Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityPortSecurity.description: default: 6(Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityThermalProtec.description: default: 6(Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fTrapEventSeverityWarmStart.description: default: 4(Warning) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fSMTPMailServer.description: Up to 47 characters describing email server.

mgs360024fSMTPUserName.name: mgs360024fSMTPUserName
mgs360024fSMTPUserName.description: Up to 47 characters describing user name.

mgs360024fSMTPServeriryLevel.name: mgs360024fSMTPServeriryLevel
mgs360024fSMTPServeriryLevel.description: default: 6 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

mgs360024fSMTPReturnPath.description: Up to 47 characters describing return path.

mgs360024fSMTPEmailAddress6.description: Up to 47 characters describing mail address.

mgs360024fACLPortsConfPortRedirect.name: mgs360024fACLPortsConfPortRedirect
mgs360024fACLPortsConfPortRedirect.description: default: 0 0: Disable range : 0 - end port number

mgs360024fACLPortsConfCounter.name: mgs360024fACLPortsConfCounter
mgs360024fACLPortsConfCounter.description: Counts the number of frames that match this ACE.

mgs360024fACLACECreate.name: mgs360024fACLACECreate
mgs360024fACLACECreate.description: default: 0 0 : None (read only) 1 : Create an ACE entry

mgs360024fACLACEID.name: mgs360024fACLACEID
mgs360024fACLACEID.description: If the ACE ID is specified and an entry with this ACE ID already exists, the ACE will be modified. Otherwise, a new ACE will be added. range : 1 - 256.

mgs360024fACLACENextID.name: mgs360024fACLACENextID
mgs360024fACLACENextID.description: If the next ACE ID is non zero, the ACE will be placed before this ACE in the list. If the next ACE ID is zero, the ACE will be placed last in the list. range : 0 - 256.

mgs360024fACLACEIngressPort.name: mgs360024fACLACEIngressPort
mgs360024fACLACEIngressPort.description: Indicates the ingress port of the ACE. Possible values are: All: The ACE will match all ingress port. Port: The ACE will match a specific ingress port.Format: 1,3,6.

mgs360024fACLACEFrameType.name: mgs360024fACLACEFrameType
mgs360024fACLACEFrameType.description: 0: any, 1: arp, 2: etype, 3: icmp, 4: ipv4, 5: tcp, 6: udp.

mgs360024fACLACEDenyPortRedirect.name: mgs360024fACLACEDenyPortRedirect
mgs360024fACLACEDenyPortRedirect.description: Frames that hit the ACE are redirected to the port number specified here. Disabled: indicates that the port redirect operation is disabled. Port Format: 1,3,6.

mgs360024fACLACELogging.name: mgs360024fACLACELogging
mgs360024fACLACELogging.description: default: 0, 0: disable - Frames matching the ACE are not logged. 1: enable - Frames matching the ACE are stored in the system log.

mgs360024fACLACEShutdown.name: mgs360024fACLACEShutdown
mgs360024fACLACEShutdown.description: default: 0, 0: disable - Port shut down is disabled for the AC. 1: enable - If a frame matches the ACE, the ingress port will be disabled.

mgs360024fACLACEVLANTagPriority.name: mgs360024fACLACEVLANTagPriority
mgs360024fACLACEVLANTagPriority.description: Specify the tag priority for this ACE. The tag priority can't be set when 802.1Q Tagged is disabled default: 8, 8: Any, range : 0 - 8

mgs360024fACLACEVLANVID.name: mgs360024fACLACEVLANVID
mgs360024fACLACEVLANVID.description: Specify the VLAN ID filter for this ACE. The vid can't be set when 802.1Q Tagged is disabled. default: 0, 0: Any - No VLAN ID filter is specified. range : 0 - 4094

mgs360024fACLACEEtherType.name: mgs360024fACLACEEtherType
mgs360024fACLACEEtherType.description: 0: Any - Any but excluding 0x0800(IPv4) 0x0806(ARP) and 0x86DD(IPv6). range : 0 or 1536(0x0600)- 65535(0xffff).

mgs360024fACLACESMAC.name: mgs360024fACLACESMAC
mgs360024fACLACESMAC.description: Configure source MAC address for this ACE. <mac-address>: A frame that hits this ACE matches this source MAC address value. Any: Don't care.

mgs360024fACLACEDMACType.name: mgs360024fACLACEDMACType
mgs360024fACLACEDMACType.description: DMAC Type. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: Broadcast - Frame must be broadcast. 2: Unicast - Frame must be unicast. 3: Multicast - Frame must be multicast. 4: mac address range : 0 - 4

mgs360024fACLACEDMAC.name: mgs360024fACLACEDMAC
mgs360024fACLACEDMAC.description: Configure destination MAC address for this ACE. <mac-address>: A frame that hits this ACE matches this destination MAC address value. Any: Don't care. Broadcast: Frame must be broadcast. Unicast: Frame must be unicast. Multicast: Frame must be multicast.

mgs360024fACLACEArpOpcode.name: mgs360024fACLACEArpOpcode
mgs360024fACLACEArpOpcode.description: Configure ARP opcode for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: arp. 2: rarp. 3: other. 4: No data. range : 0 - 3

mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply.name: mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply
mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply.description: Specify the available ARP/RARP opcode (OP) flag for this ACE. default: 2, 0: Frame must have ARP Reply or RARP Reply OP flag. 1: Frame must have ARP Request or RARP Request OP flag set. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac.name: mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac
mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their sender hardware address field (SHA) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP frames where SHA is not equal to the SMAC address. 1: ARP frames where SHA is equal to the SMAC address. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac.name: mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac
mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their target hardware address field (THA) settings. default: 2, 0: RARP frames where THA is not equal to the DMAC address. 1: RARP frames where THA is equal to the DMAC address. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsLength.name: mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsLength
mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsLength.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP hardware address length (HLN) and protocol address length (PLN) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the HLN is not equal to Ethernet(0x06) or the (PLN) is not equal to IPv4(0x04). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the HLN is equal to Ethernet (0x06) and the (PLN) is equal to IPv4(0x04). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsIp.name: mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsIp
mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsIp.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP hardware address space (HRD) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the HLD is not equal to Ethernet(1). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the HLD is equal to Ethernet(1). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet.name: mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet
mgs360024fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP protocol address space (PRO) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the PRO is not equal to IP\n(0x800). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the PRO is equal to IP(0x800). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

mgs360024fACLACESIPType.name: mgs360024fACLACESIPType
mgs360024fACLACESIPType.description: Configure source IP address for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: IP Address. 2: No data. range : 0 - 1

mgs360024fACLACESIPIPAddress.name: mgs360024fACLACESIPIPAddress
mgs360024fACLACESIPIPAddress.description: A frame that hits this ACE matches this source IP address value.

mgs360024fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix.name: mgs360024fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix
mgs360024fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix.description: Network prefix. default: 32, 0: No data. range : 1 - 32

mgs360024fACLACEDIPType.name: mgs360024fACLACEDIPType
mgs360024fACLACEDIPType.description: Configure destination IP address for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: IP Address. 2: No data. range : 0 - 1

mgs360024fACLACEDIPIPAddress.name: mgs360024fACLACEDIPIPAddress
mgs360024fACLACEDIPIPAddress.description: A frame that hits this ACE matches this destination IP address value.

mgs360024fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix.name: mgs360024fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix
mgs360024fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix.description: Network prefix. default: 32, 0: No data. range : 1 - 32

mgs360024fACLACEIPProtocol.name: mgs360024fACLACEIPProtocol
mgs360024fACLACEIPProtocol.description: Configure IP protocol for this ACE. default: 256, 256: Any - Don't care. 257: No data. range : 0 - 256

mgs360024fACLACEIPFlagsTTL.name: mgs360024fACLACEIPFlagsTTL
